node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
Welcome to Oktoberfest weekend!

We can't wait to raise a liter with you all this weekend. Celebrations will take place today and tomorrow from Noon - 6 PM, with normal operations to follow afterward on each day.

Our Oktoberfest lager will be pouring at all four locations and commemorative glassware and t-shirts are ready for you to take home in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point.

For those of you planning to visit Canton, please follow the direction of our parking attendants when you arrive. They'll ensure you're parked and ready to enjoy the festivities ASAP.

Prost! 🍻

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 17, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
And now, the moment we've all been *very patiently* waiting for...the return of our Oktoberfest lager!

Under the festival tents in Munich, you'll find thousands of Maß full of brilliantly clear, golden lager. Wiesnbier, the traditional Festbier of Oktoberfest, is beautiful in its simplicity.

For our take on the style, we utilized primarily German pilsner malt and paired it with noble Spalter hops to achieve notes of rich grain, bread dough, and a touch of lemon. Subtly sweet on the palate, with a medium-bodied mouthfeel, this is a lager built for enjoying by the mug.

Cans will be ready to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for Pickup in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point, as well as for UPS Direct. $15.20/4-pack. You can most certainly expect it on draft at all four locations throughout the weekend as well!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on September 17, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
We've got a few unique wares for you to celebrate Oktoberfest with this year. Available in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point this weekend, as well as our online merch store and UPS Direct starting tomorrow at 9 AM:

1L Maßkrug* - This heavy-duty, dimpled stein can withstand even the most enthusiastic of "Prost's"! Enjoy your first pour of our Oktoberfest Wiesnbier as it's meant to be enjoyed. $20/glass. $16/1L pour in the glass.

Unisex Oktoberfest Tees - A seasonal take on our classic logo t-shirts, these limited tees sport a custom logo on the front, with the Trillium Oktoberfest crest on the back neck. $20/t-shirt.

We can't wait to see you this weekend! 🍻

*Please note - while glassware will be available to purchase on-site at all locations, it will not be listed on our Toast pickup pages for pre-order.

node.text:
There's an unsung stunner of a shareable dish currently on the Canton menu that we'd encourage you to try before summer's official end.

Featuring local green beans tossed in a Trillium Farm smoked tomato vinaigrette, our Green Bean Salad is served with cashew cheese and topped with maple sugar flax crackers.

It's balanced, complex, and will make you rethink how delicious green beans can be. It just so happens to be gluten-free and vegetarian as well! Give it a try next time you stop by.

We're just two days away from our 2021 Oktoberfest celebration! Stay tuned for details regarding a special beer release, as well as some limited gear drops.

Which location will you be joining us at?

node.text:
Situated on an idyllic farm in Salem, CT just 30 miles from the Trillium Farm, lies @foxfarmbeer. For our first collaboration together, we leaned heavily into shared values, highlighting two small, local maltsters that each brewery has worked with extensively.

Brewed with pilsner malt from @valleymalt in Hadley, MA, and both biscuit and pilsner malt from @thrallfamilymalt in Windsor, CT, Thresh is a Pale Lager with just a touch of modern flair, achieved with a very subtle dry-hop of Motueka.

Presenting a brilliantly clear pale gold, we taste fresh-baked biscuit, rising bread dough, and a fleeting highlight of key lime. Order cans online tomorrow for both Pickup and UPS Direct. $15.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

node.text:
Born in 2020, The Avenue Series was the self-evident extension to our foundational Street Series of single hop-focused IPAs. The larger Double IPAs represented our growth beyond Fort Point while paying homage to the many historic roadways throughout our home of greater Boston.

As we've done with both The Streets and The Harbor Islands, The Avenues resembles the pinnacle of its respective series. We've crafted an amplified grist bill with plenty of wheat for a soft mouthfeel, and combined an array of hops that define choice beers throughout the series.

Hopped with Citra, Mosaic, Nelson Sauvin, and Simcoe, The Avenues is a strikingly aromatic Triple IPA. Palate-coating, yet balanced and highly drinkable, cans will be ready to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct.

It’s time to dust off the dirndl and lederhosen!

On Saturday, 9/18, and Sunday, 9/19, we will celebrate Oktoberfest 2021 at all four Trillium locations. Each site will offer a unique experience, with food specials, tapping of our traditional Wiesnbier, music, and more.

To learn more, check out our story, which you’ll be able to reference on our profile as a highlight.

First released in November of 2018, we find ourselves once again craving Coffee Cake as we head towards a New England autumn. 

Brewed with Vietnamese cinnamon, Trillium Blend from @barringtoncoffee, and Madagascar vanilla, Coffee Cake returns for a special Saturday release!

500ml bottles are $20.05 each, with a limit of four bottles per person. They'll be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct.

node.text:
Utilizing a blend of Vermont Smoke & Cure pepperoni, pancetta, and prosciutto, our take on the traditional N'duja is topped with Herb Ricotta, Broccoli Raab, and Trillium Farm Cherry Tomatoes that have been roasted in our wood-fired ovens.

Just one bite will make it clear why it's quickly becoming a favorite in Canton!
